ly%2C%C2%A0Lao%20Rongzhi%20had%20been%20on%20the%20run%20for%2020%20years%20after%20being%20engaged%20in%20a%20series%20of%20crimes%2C%20including%20robbery%2C%20extortion%2C%20and%20brutal%20murder%20of%20seven%20people%2C%20between%201996%20and%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20arrested%20by%20police%20in%20Xiamen%2C%20Fujian%20Province%2C%20on%20November%2028%2C%202019.%C2%A0Jiangxi%20Provincial%20High%20People's%20Court%20last%20year%20upheld%20her%20death%20sentence%20as%20it%20heard%20her%20appeal.%20During%20the%20trial%2C%C2%A0she%20claimed%20her%20involvement%20in%20the%20crimes%20stopped%20at%20kidnapping%20and%20robbery%20and%20blamed%20her%20ex-boyfriend%2C%20who%20had%20been%20executed%20in%201999%2C%20for%20the%20murders%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fpeople-culture%2Fsocial-welfare%2Farticle%2F3148161%2Fchinas-notorious-female-serial-killer-lao%5C%22%3ESouth%20China%20Morning%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20that%C2%A0Lao%20conspired%20with%20her%20ex-boyfriend%2C%20Fa%20Ziying%2C%20to%20kidnap%2C%20rob%2C%20and%20murder%20seven%20people%20in%20four%20different%20cities%20including%20Nanchang%2C%20Wenzhou%2C%20Changzhou%2C%20and%20Hefei.%20In%20one%20case%20in%201996%2C%20they%20murdered%20a%20couple%20and%20their%20three-year-old%20child%20before%20robbing%20their%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%C2%A0rejected%20Lao%20and%20her%20lawyer's%20claims%20that%20she%20played%20a%20minor%20role%20in%20the%20series%20of%20crimes%20and%20only%20assisted%20her%20boyfriend.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20trial%2C%20she%20also%20tearfully%20apologized%20to%20the%20victims'%20families%20and%20offered%20compensation%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Chinese%20media%2C%20Lao%C2%A0targeted%20victims%20while%20providing%20services%20at%20entertainment%20venues%2C%20while%20Fa%20killed%20them.%C2%A0Fa%20was%20apprehended%20in%201999%20when%20col