y-67747949.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Ftechnology-67747949.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20Can%20Take%20Over%20Any%20Mobile%20Network%20For%20Public%20Safety%2C%20Says%20Draft%20Law%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20can%20take%20temporary%20possession%20of%20any%20telecommunication%20network%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20public%20safety%20or%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20public%20emergency%2C%20the%20proposed%20law%20for%20telecommunications%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telecommunications%20Bill%202023%20was%20introduced%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20today%20by%20Communications%20Minister%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw%20amid%20the%20Opposition's%20protest%20demanding%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah's%20statement%20on%20the%20breach%20in%20Parliament%20security%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20law%20states%2C%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20occurrence%20of%20any%20public%20emergency%2C%20including%20disaster%20management%2C%20or%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20public%20safety%2C%20the%20Central%20Government%20or%20a%20State%20Government%20or%20any%20officer%20specially%20authorised%20in%20this%20behalf%20by%20the%20Central%20Government%20or%20a%20State%20Government%2C%20if%20satisfied%20that%20it%20is%20necessary%20or%20expedient%20so%20to%20do%2C%20by%20notification-%20(a)%20take%20temporary%20possession%20of%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20or%20telecommunication%20network%20from%20an%20authorised%20entity...%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20states%20that%20messages%20from%20mediapersons%20with%20accreditation%20shall%20not%20be%20intercepted%20unless%20their%20transmission%20is%20prohibited%20under%20the%20national%20security%20clause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20press%20messages%2C%20intended%20to%20be%20published%20in%20India%2C%20of%20correspondents%20accredited%20to%20the%20Central%20Government%20or%20a%20State%20Government%20shall%20not%20be%20intercepted%20or%20detained%2C%20unless%20their%20transmission%20has%20been%20prohibited%20under%20clause%20(a)%20of%20sub-section%20(2)%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20draft%20Bill%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20law%20also%20states%20that%20the%20government%20may%2C%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20public%20safety%2C%20direct%20the%20interception%20of%20any%20message%20between%20individuals.%20It%20also%20empowers%20the%20government%20to%20suspend%20telecommunication%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20states%20that%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20defence%20and%20security%20of%20the%20State%2C%20the%20Centre%20can%20%26quot%3Bdirect%20that%20any%20message%20or%20class%20of%20messages%2C%20to%20or%20from%20any%20person%20or%20class%20of%20persons%2C%20to%20or%20from%20any%20telecommunication%20equipment%20or%20class%20of%20telecommunication%20equipment%2C%20or%20relating%20to%20any%20particular%20subject%2C%20brought%20for%20transmission%20by%2C%20or%20transmitted%20or%20received%20by%20any%20telecommunication%20service%20or%20telecommunication%20network%2C%20shall%20not%20be%20transmitted%2C%20or%20shall%20be%20intercepted%20or%20detained%2C%20or%20shall%20be%20disclosed%20in%20intelligible%20format%20to%20the%20officer%20mentioned%20in%20such%20order%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20also%20says%20that%20unlawful%20interception%20of%20messages%20may%20attract%20jail%20term%20of%20up%20to%20three%20years%2C%20a%20fine%20up%20to%20Rs%202%20crore%20or%20both.%C2%A0The%20draft%20also%20provides%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20Telecom%20Disputes%20Settlement%20and%20Appellate%20Tribunal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20law%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Telegraph%20Act%201885%2C%20Indian%20Wireless%20Telegraphy%20Act%201933%20and%20Telegraph%20Wires%20(Unlawful%20Possession)%20Act%2C%201950.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government's%20contention%20some%20of%20these%20laws%20are%20as%20old%20as%20138%20years%20and%20a%20new%20law%20is%20needed%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20rapidly%20emerging%20technologies%20in%20communication.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20NDTV%20on%20the%20Bill%2C%20BSP%20MP%20Ritesh%20Pandey%20pointed%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20on%20the%20right%20to%20privacy.%20%26quot%3BThis%20raises%20a%20question%20mark%20on%20this%20Bill.%20The%20Puttaswamy%20judgment%20(right%20to%20privacy%20verdict)%20held%20that%20data%20needs%20to%20be%20anonymised%2C%20but%20in%20this%20case%2C%20that%20data%20can%20be%20linked%20to%20an%20individual%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20NDTV%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20ramifications%20of%20the%20draft%20law%20need%20to%20be%20looked%20into%2C%20particularly%20with%20regard%20to%20backward%20communities%20who%20lack%20adequate%20awareness%20of%20technology%20and%20their%20right%20to%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20hope%20that%20by%20the%20time%20this%20Bill%20is%20implemented%2C%20these%20questions%20will%20be%20looked%20into%20and%20privacy%20rights%20will%20be%20safeguarded%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Pandey%20had%20raised%20his%20concerns%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20today%20before%20proceedings%20were%20adjourned%20amid%20protests%20by%20the%20Opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702898520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2F3u76hn_mobile-phone-_625x300_25_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcentre-can-take-over-any-mobile-network-for-public-safety-says-draft-law-4695903%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Centre%20can%20take%20temporary%20possession%20of%20any%20telecommunication%20network%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20public%20safety%20or%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20public%20emergency%2C%20the%20proposed%20law%20for%20telecommunications%20states.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcentre-can-take-over-any-mobile-network-for-public-safety-says-draft-law-4695903%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcentre-can-take-over-any-mobile-network-for-public-safety-says-draft-law-4695903%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcentre-can-take-over-any-mobile-network-for-public-safety-says-draft-law-4695903%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Divorce%20Proceedings%20Stayed%20As%20Wife%20Seeks%20Husband's%20Cooperation%20In%20IVF%20Process%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20stayed%20the%20divorce%20proceedings%20between%20an%20estranged%20couple%20after%20the%20wife%20sought%20her%20husband's%20cooperation%20to%20conceive%20through%20in-vitro%20fertilisation%20(IVF)%20process%20for%20which%20she%20wants%20his%20sperm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20has%20moved%20the%20top%20court%20seeking%20transfer%20of%20the%20pending%20divorce%20case%20filed%20by%20her%20husband%20in%20Bhopal%20to%20Lucknow%20where%20she%20currently%20lives%20with%20her%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20transfer%20petition%20came%20up%20for%20hearing%20before%20a%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Pankaj%20Mithal%20who%20agreed%20to%20hear%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20divorce%20petition%20between%20the%20parties%20is%20pending%20at%20family%20court%2C%20Bhopal.%20Petitioner-wife%20is%20residing%20at%20Lucknow%20and%20wants%20the%20same%20to%20be%20transferred%20to%20Lucknow.%20Issue%20notice%20(to%20husband)%20returnable%20within%20six%20weeks%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said%20in%20its%20order%20passed%20on%20December%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20there%20shall%20be%20a%20stay%20of%20further%20proceedings%20in%20(divorce%20case)%E2%80%A6%20pending%20before%20the%20court%20of%20principal%20judge%2C%20family%20court%2C%20Bhopal%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Asad%20Alvi%20appeared%20for%20the%20woman%20in%20the%20apex%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20plea%2C%20the%2044-year-old%20woman%20said%20the%20couple%20had%20married%20in%20November%202017%20and%2C%20despite%20repeated%20request%2C%20her%20husband%20used%20his%20unemployment%20as%20an%20excuse%20to%20delay%20parenthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20said%20after%20persistent%20requests%2C%20in%20March%20this%20year%2C%20her%20husband%20agreed%20to%20have%20a%20child%20through%20IVF%20for%20which%20they%20underwent%20various%20medical%20tests%20and%20started%20taking%20the%20required%20medication%20under%20the%20care%20of%20a%20doctor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20to%20the%20petitioner's%20shock%20and%20dismay%2C%20the%20respondent%20(husband)%20abruptly%20filed%20for%20divorce%20%E2%80%A6while%20the%20IVF%20treatment%20was%20underway.%20He%20severed%20all%20contact%20with%20the%20petitioner%2C%20blocking%20her%20calls%2C%20and%20leaving%20her%20emotionally%20stranded%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20plea%2C%20filed%20through%20advocate%20Aishwarya%20Pathak%2C%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20seeking%20transfer%20of%20the%20pending%20divorce%20case%20to%20Lucknow%2C%20the%20petition%20said%20the%20woman%20was%20ousted%20from%20her%20matrimonial%20home%20and%20she%20faces%20significant%20challenges%20defending%20it%20in%20Bhopal%20as%20she%20is%20living%20with%20her%20parents%20in%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20petition%2C%20she%20has%20also%20filed%20an%20application%20seeking%20a%20direction%20to%20her%20husband%20%26quot%3Bto%20co-operate%20with%20petitioner%20and%20the%20doctors%20in%20the%20IVF%20process%20and%20provide%20sperm%20and%20other%20co-operation%20whenever%20it%20is%20needed%20or%20advised%20by%20the%20IVF%20doctors%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plea%20said%20after%20their%20marriage%2C%20the%20man%20revealed%20his%20unemployment%20and%20requested%20the%20woman%20to%20stay%20with%20her%20parents%20temporarily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20assured%20her%20that%20they%20would%20have%20a%20child%20when%20he%20secured%20stable%20employment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20woman%20has%20said%20in%20the%20petition%2C%20adding%20he%20later%20secured%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%E2%80%A6after%20great%20persuasion%20the%20respondent%20agreed%20to%20have%20a%20child%20as%20such%20the%20petitioner%20is%20around%2044%20years%20old%20and%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20menopause%2C%20doctor%20advised%20them%20to%20have%20a%20child%20by%20IVF%20process%20before%20the%20completing%20the%20age%20of%2045%2F46%20years.%20Both%20agreed%20and%20started%20treatment%20to%20undergo%20the%20IVF%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20plea%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702898460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fc5p4n3lg_supreme-court-premises_625x300_22_November_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdivorce-proceedings-stayed-as-wife-seeks-husbands-cooperation-in-ivf-process-4696654%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20stayed%20the%20divorce%20proceedings%20between%20an%20estranged%20couple%20after%20the%20wife%20sought%20her%20husband's%20cooperation%20to%20conceive%20through%20in-vitro%20fertilisation%20(IVF)%20process%20for%20which%20she%20wants%20his%20sperm.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdivorce-proceedings-stayed-as-wife-seeks-husbands-cooperation-in-ivf-process-4696654%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdivorce-proceedings-stayed-as-wife-seeks-husbands-cooperation-in-ivf-process-4696654%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdivorce-proceedings-stayed-as-wife-seeks-husbands-cooperation-in-ivf-process-4696654%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Essential%20Public%20Recruitment%26nbsp%3BCan%20Help%20Bihar%20Break%20Cycle%20of%20Poverty%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F18163834%2FDeoria-Medical-College-Hospital-Heatwave-Deaths.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECompelling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fdevelopmentwithh0000unse%2Fpage%2Fn9%2Fmode%2F2up%5C%22%3Eempirical%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20developing%20countries%20that%20achieved%20high%20human%20development%20and%20economic%20indicators%20(South%20Korea%2C%20Malaysia%20and%20Taiwan%20in%20Asia%3B%20Costa%20Rica%20in%20Latin%20America)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eshows%20how%20certain%20threshold%20levels%20of%20public%20employment%2C%20especially%20in%20sectors%20like%20education%2C%20healthcare%20and%20police%2C%20not%20only%20develop%20needed%20human%20capital%20for%20economic%20growth%20but%20is%20good%20for%20human%20well%20being.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20in%20a%20state%20like%20Bihar%2C%20which%20has%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2021%2F38%2Fspecial-articles%2Fwhy-human-development-should-precede-economic.html%5C%22%3Elowest%20human%20development%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%20(HDI)%20among%20Indian%20states%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ethe%20case%20for%20massively%20enhancing%20public%20employment%20in%20these%20essential%20areas%20becomes%20even%20more%20pertinent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20huge%20vacancies%20in%20these%20three%20sectors%20in%20the%20state.%20If%20they%20are%20not%20filled%2C%20there%20is%20little%20possibility%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20health%20services%20or%20education%20can%20improve.%20In%20their%20absence%2C%20Bihar%20cannot%20have%20more%20employment%20at%20home%2C%20and%20will%20remain%20a%20state%20whose%20economy%20survives%20upon%20subsistence%20agriculture%2C%20growing%20services%2C%20or%20migrant%20remittances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20there%20is%20little%20prospect%20of%20investment%20in%20Bihar%20picking%20up%20despite%20the%20Investment%20Summit%20organised%20by%20the%20Bihar%20government%20on%20December%2011-13%2C%202023%20if%20the%20quality%20of%20local%20governance%20does%20not%20improve.%20Some%20studies%20suggest%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20operations%20of%20organised%20crime%2C%20often%20local%2C%20are%20a%20reason%20for%20the%20deindustrialisation%20that%20Bihar%20has%20suffered%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades.%20Hence%2C%20it%20is%20critical%20that%20there%20are%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20sufficient%20policemen%20to%20address%20the%20problem%20(though%20their%20political%20capture%20needs%20to%20be%20precluded).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOwing%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20publicly%20available%20official%20data%20on%20total%20state%20government%20employment%20in%20Bihar%2C%20our%20analysis%20is%20based%20on%20employment%20data%20in%20sector-specific%20Union%20and%20state%20government%20reports%20but%20also%20investigative%20news%20media%20reports%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20of%202022%2C%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20total%20state%20government%20employment%2C%20including%20permanent%20and%20contractual%20employees%2C%20stood%20at%20close%20to%204.5%20lakh.%20Almost%2085%25%20of%20this%20was%20formed%20by%20the%20three%20sectors%20of%20education%20(including%20school%20and%20higher%20education)%2C%20health%20and%20police.%20Hence%2C%20it%20is%20critical%20to%20scrutinise%20these%20three%20segments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBihar%E2%80%99s%20schools%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBihar%E2%80%99s%20government%20schools%20are%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20employer%2C%20like%20other%20Indian%20states.%20As%20per%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Ministry%20of%20Education%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EUnified%20District%20Information%20System%20for%20Education%20Plus%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EUDISE%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2B)%2C%20till%20FY%E2%80%9922%2C%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20government%20schools%20had%204%20lakh%20teachers%20%E2%80%93%20out%20of%20which%20close%20to%203.5%20lakh%20were%20on%20contract.%20This%20gave%20a%20Pupil%20Teacher%20Ratio%20(PTR)%20of%2055.28%2C%20much%20higher%20than%20states%20like%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(33)%2C%20Maharashtra%20(30.40)%2C%20West%20Bengal%20(34.88)%2C%20Karnataka%20(28.69)%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20(24.52).%20To%20meet%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.education.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fupload_files%2Fmhrd%2Ffiles%2FNEP_Final_English_0.pdf%5C%22%3EPTR%20benchmark%20of%2030%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20stipulated%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20National%20Education%20Policy%20(NEP)%2C%20Bihar%20needed%20a%20staggering%203.38%20lakh%20more%20government%20school%20teachers%20in%20FY22.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20state%20had%202.2%20lakh%20government%20teacher%20vacancies%20based%20on%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20sanctioned%20posts%20till%20FY22.%20The%20situation%20came%20to%20a%20head%20because%20successive%20governments%20failed%20to%20conduct%20any%20permanent%20recruitment%20while%20insufficient%20contractual%20hiring%20remained%20mired%20in%20court%20cases%20and%20public%20protests.%20It%20is%20only%20in%202023%20that%20some%20strong%20green%20shoots%20appeared%20with%20the%20hiring%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fbihar-government-recruits-1-2-lakh-teachers-through-single-advertisement%2Fcid%2F1977213%23%5C%22%3E1.2%20lakh%20permanent%20teachers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20one%20go%2C%20a%20record%20of%20sorts.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20no%20data%20available%20on%20how%20many%20of%20those%20recruited%20were%20already%20working%20as%20contractual%20teachers%20or%20how%20many%20are%20from%20other%20states.%20If%20people%20from%20these%20two%20categories%20were%20in%20high%20numbers%2C%20the%20sector%E2%80%99s%20problems%20will%20not%20subside%20anytime%20soon.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20higher%20education%2C%20the%20number%20of%20sanctioned%20vacancies%20was%20close%20to%2022%2C000%20(over%2013%2C500%20teaching%20and%20over%208%2C000%20non-teaching%20positions)%20as%20of%20early%202022.%20These%20numbers%20grew%20rapidly%20in%20recent%20years%20owing%20to%20newer%20universities%20and%20colleges%20opening%20without%20commensurate%20hiring.%20So%20sanctioned%20vacancies%20are%2050-80%25.%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20higher%20education%20PTR%20is%2060%2C%20while%20the%20pan-India%20figure%20was%2024%20(All%20India%20Survey%20on%20Higher%20Education%202020-21).%20Unlike%20school%20education%2C%20employment%20in%20the%20Bihar%20government%E2%80%99s%20higher%20educational%20institutions%20has%20not%20been%20revived.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02184742%2FBihar-job-mahakumbh.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02184742%2FBihar-job-mahakumbh.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02184742%2FBihar-job-mahakumbh-300x141.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02184742%2FBihar-job-mahakumbh-1024x480.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683213%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22563%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAppointment%20letter%20recipients%20in%20Patna.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHealth%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20most%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20public%20healthcare%20system%20was%20laid%20bare%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20Even%20the%20few%2C%20better-known%20city%20government%20hospitals%20have%20corridors%20to%20courtyards%20filled%20with%20suffering%20patients%20and%20unattended%20corpses.%20WHO%20prescribes%20there%20should%20be%201%20doctor%20per%201%2C000%20persons%20in%20any%20country%20or%20administrative%20unit%3B%20the%20Bihar%20assembly%20was%20told%20that%20the%20state%20had%201%20government%20doctor%20per%2022%2C000.%20In%20a%20poor%20country%2C%20especially%20Bihar%20whose%20per%20capita%20income%20is%20one-third%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20average%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20people%20entirely%20depend%20on%20public%20healthcare.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20numbers%20for%20sanctioned%20vacancies%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eshortfall%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(the%20latter%20based%20on%20national%20or%20international%20benchmarks)%20vary%20with%20every%20source.%20The%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20and%20Family%20Welfare%E2%80%99s%202021-22%20Rural%20Health%20Statistics%20report%20put%20sanctioned%20vacancies%20in%20Bihar%20at%20over%2058%2C400%20and%20the%20total%20shortfall%20based%20on%20Indian%20Public%20Health%20Standards%20benchmarks%20at%20over%2064%2C300.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20a%202021-22%20report%20by%20Bihar%20Health%20Society%20put%20sanctioned%20vacancies%20at%20close%20to%2038%2C000.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPolice%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20third%20major%20recruiter%20in%20the%20Bihar%20government%20is%20the%20police.%20UN%20prescribes%20at%20least%20222%20police%20personnel%20per%20lakh%20population.%20Indian%20home%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20Bureau%20of%20Police%20Research%20and%20Development%20(BPRD)%20stated%20that%20until%20January%201%2C%202022%2C%20to%20meet%20the%20UN%20benchmark%2C%20the%20Bihar%20police%20needed%20an%20additional%201.82%20lakh%20employees.%20That%20figure%20is%2039%2C000%20more%20than%20the%20total%20employed%20strength%20of%20Bihar%20Police%20of%201.43%20lakh.%20As%20of%20mid-2023%2C%2075%2C000%20sanctioned%20vacancies%20existed.%20The%20consequence%20of%20this%20gross%20neglect%20over%20decades%20has%20been%20that%20Bihar%20had%20India%E2%80%99s%20highest%20number%20of%20land%20and%20property-related%20crimes%20and%20ranked%20second%20in%20murders%20and%20murder%20attempts%2C%20rapes%20and%20crimes%20against%20Dalits%20(National%20Crime%20Records%20Bureau%2C%202021).%20However%2C%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20policing%20has%20seen%20some%20silver%20lining%20with%20nearly%2010%2C500%20personnel%20hired%20in%20one%20go%20in%20late%202022%20and%20the%20recruitment%20of%20another%2022%2C650%20already%20underway.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStill%2C%20the%20total%20workforce%20shortage%20in%20Bihar%20in%20the%20above%20three%20sectors%20%E2%80%93%20based%20on%20national%20and%20international%20benchmarks%20%E2%80%93%20stood%20at%20almost%206%20lakh%20as%20of%202022%2C%20while%20sanctioned%20vacancies%20were%20over%203.75%20lakh.%20This%20has%20kept%20the%20quality%20of%20public%20service%20delivery%20in%20Bihar%20at%20rock%20bottom%20for%20decades.%20The%20state%E2%80%99s%20financial%20situation%20owing%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20productive%20investments%20has%20seen%20Bihar%20endure%20declining%20tax%20revenues%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20GSDP%20while%20being%20unable%20to%20utilise%20Union%20government%20funds%20worth%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20crores.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20where%20public%20sector%20hiring%20in%20human%20well-being%20areas%20like%20education%2C%20healthcare%20and%20law%20and%20order%20will%20unlock%20doors%20to%20higher%20investment%20rates%20and%20result%20in%20far%20higher%20tax%20revenues.%20Further%2C%20expanded%20hiring%20in%20high%20labour-intensive%20sectors%20like%20education%20and%20health%20(which%20employ%20a%20relatively%20higher%20proportion%20of%20women)%20will%20not%20only%20reduce%20gender%20disparities%20but%20also%20create%20higher%20disposable%20incomes%20for%20numerous%20lower%20to%20middle-income%20households%2C%20thereby%20pushing%20the%20economic%20cycle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20hub%20and%20spoke%20model%20for%20education%20with%20each%20district%20or%20municipality%20having%20a%20school%20acting%20as%20a%20hub%20and%20other%20schools%20as%20spokes%20could%20provide%20autonomy%20in%20resource%20sharing%20and%20decentralised%20decision-making.%20In%20healthcare%2C%20the%20state%20must%20aim%20for%20a%20public%20investment%20amounting%20to%202%25%20of%20GSDP%20by%202025%20and%202.5%25%20by%202027%20as%20envisaged%20in%20the%20National%20Health%20Policy%20of%202017.%20Similarly%2C%20meeting%20shortcomings%20in%20police%20in%20existing%20and%20emerging%20economic%20hubs%20on%20a%20war%20footing%20will%20bring%20in%20rapid%20investments%20which%20can%20then%20fund%20meeting%20the%20needs%20of%20backward%20areas%20within%20a%20few%20years.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHence%2C%20hiring%20more%20teachers%2C%20health%20staff%20and%20policemen%20is%20a%20must%20for%20Bihar%20to%20realise%20its%20true%20potential%20and%20a%20first%20step%20to%20emerge%20from%20its%20cycle%20of%20poverty%20and%20backwardness%20once%20and%20for%20all.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESantosh%20Mehrotra%20is%20a%20Professorial%20Fellow%20(Economics)%2C%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Museum%20%26amp%3B%20Library%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%20and%20the%20lead%20author%20of%20a%20new%20report%20on%20creating%20employment%20with%20growth%20in%20Bihar.%20Anchal%20Gupta%20is%20a%20graduate%20student%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Ottawa%2C%20Canada%2C%20in%20aeronautical%20engineering%2C%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Bihar%20report%20team%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702898432000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F18163834%2FDeoria-Medical-College-Hospital-Heatwave-Deaths.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fessential-public-recruitment-can-help-bihar-break-cycle-of-poverty%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Employment%20in%20sectors%20like%20education%2C%20healthcare%20and%20police%2C%20not%20only%20develop%20needed%20human%20capital%20for%20economic%20growth%20but%20is%20good%20for%20human%20well%20being.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fessential-public-recruitment-can-help-bihar-break-cycle-of-poverty%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20next%20for%20Chouhan%3F%20Ex-MP%20CM%20to%20meet%20Nadda%20tomorrow%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702898381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106094936%2Cimgsize-39340.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fformer-madhya-pradesh-cm-shivraj-singh-chouhan-to-meet-bjp-president-jp-nadda-amid-buzz-over-future-responsibility%2Farticleshow%2F106090865.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%20will%20meet%20BJP%20president%20JP%20Nadda%20in%20the%20national%20capital%20on%20Tuesday%20amid%20buzz%20that%20he%20may%20be%20given%20a%20new%20responsibility%20by%20the%20party.%26quot%3BBJP%20chief%20Nadda%20has%20called%20for%20a%20meeting%20and%20I%20will%20go%20to%20meet%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20Chouhan%20said.The%20Chouhan-era%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20came%20to%20an%20end%20last%20week%20after%20BJP%20replaced%20the%20four-time%20chief%20minister%20with%20Ujjain%20South%20MLA%20Mohan%20Yadav.%20Since%20stepping%20down%20from%20the%20post%20after%20nearly%2016.5%20years%2C%20there%20have%20been%20speculations%20about%20the%20next%20assignment%20for%20the%2064-year-old.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fformer-madhya-pradesh-cm-shivraj-singh-chouhan-to-meet-bjp-president-jp-nadda-amid-buzz-over-future-responsibility%2Farticleshow%2F106090865.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20Survey%20Report%20Submitted%20In%20Court%20By%20Archaeological%20Body%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Fgyanvapi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGyanvapi%3C%2Fa%3E%20mosque%20'scientific%20survey'%20report%20has%20been%20submitted%20to%20a%20court%20of%20the%20district%20judge%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh's%20Varanasi%20by%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India.%20The%20report%20was%20submitted%20as%20a%20sealed%20document%20on%20Monday%20afternoon.%20It%20is%20unclear%20if%20this%20will%20be%20made%20public%2C%20or%20shared%20with%20either%20the%20Hindu%20side%2C%20who%20are%20the%20petitioners%2C%20or%20the%20Muslim%20side.%20The%20next%20date%20of%20hearing%20has%20been%20fixed%20for%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Muslim%20side%20opposed%20a%20public%20report%2C%20while%20the%20Hindu%20side%20has%20objected%20to%20a%20sealed%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20of%20the%20mosque%20premises%2C%20excluding%20a%20section%20sealed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20was%20ordered%20by%20the%20Varanasi%20court%20to%20check%20if%20the%20late-17th%20century%20mosque%20was%20built%20over%20a%20Hindu%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERight-wing%20groups%20claim%20a%20temple%20was%20demolished%2C%20by%20order%20of%20Mughal%20emperor%20Aurangzeb%2C%20to%20make%20room%20for%20the%20mosque%2C%20which%20is%20adjacent%20to%20the%20iconic%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20started%20after%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20upheld%20the%20Varanasi%20court%20order.%20The%20High%20Court%20said%20the%20survey%20was%20%26quot%3Bnecessary%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20justice%26quot%3B%20and%20would%20benefit%20both%20sides%20in%20the%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20committee%20then%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20High%20Court's%20order%20but%2C%20on%20August%204%2C%20refused%20a%20stay%3B%20a%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20however%2C%20directed%20the%20ASI%20to%20not%20carry%20out%20invasive%20acts%2C%20which%20ruled%20out%20excavations%20the%20Varanasi%20court%20had%20cleared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20ordered%20non-invasive%20methods%20of%20survey%20and%20said%20certain%20areas%20-%20including%20a%20structure%20found%20in%20a%20video%20survey%20in%20April%20last%20year%20and%20claimed%20by%20petitioners%20as%20a%20'%3Cem%3Eshivling%3C%2Fem%3E'%20-%20were%20off-limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20after%20the%20mosque%20management%20committee%20claimed%20the%20ASI%20was%20digging%20in%20the%20basement%20and%20other%20places%20of%20the%20354-year-old%20complex%20without%20permission%2C%20posing%20a%20risk%20it%20might%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20row%20began%20in%20August%202021%2C%20after%20five%20Hindu%20women%20sought%20permission%20to%20pray%20at%20the%20mosque%20premises%2C%20Specifically%2C%20they%20sought%20permission%20to%20pray%20at%20a%20shrine%20behind%20the%20temple's%20western%20wall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fallahabad-high-court-reserves-verdict-in-gyanvapi-mosque-case-4646412%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAllahabad%20High%20Court%20Reserves%20Verdict%20In%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20Case%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20last%20week%20the%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20reserved%20its%20judgment%20on%20a%201991%20petition%20challenging%20the%20maintainability%20of%20a%20suit%20seekin