strations.%20From%20his%20work%20as%20an%20attorney%2C%20he%20has%20said%2C%20he%20learned%20firsthand%20how%20corrupt%20the%20courts%20were%20in%20post-Soviet%20Ukraine.%20He%20met%20the%20country's%20future%20president%20in%20about%202010%2C%20when%20his%20firm%20was%20representing%20the%20television%20channel%20Inter%2C%20where%20Zelensky%20was%20general%20producer.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20been%20sincere%20friends%20with%20Volodymyr%20Oleksandrovych%20for%20many%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Yermak%20told%20Ukrainska%20Pravda%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20ingredient%20to%20Yermak's%20success%20is%20his%20universally%20admired%20capacity%20for%20punishing%20hard%20work%2C%20around%20the%20clock.%20He%20has%20no%20spouse%20or%20children%2C%20and%20he%20has%20literally%20made%20his%20second-floor%20office%20quarters%20his%20home.%20He%20sleeps%20there%2C%20showers%20there%2C%20exercises%20there%2C%20and%20keeps%20his%20wardrobe%20there.%20In%20meals%20with%20staff%2C%20prepared%20by%20military%20cooks%2C%20he%20does%20not%20drink%20alcohol.%20Though%20he%20is%20capable%20of%20screaming%20at%20underlings%2C%20even%20those%20he%20has%20clashed%20with%20concede%20that%20he%20knows%20how%20to%20get%20things%20done.%20%26quot%3BHe%20is%20a%20very%20good%20operational%20manager%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Oleksiy%20Arestovych%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20an%20advisor%20to%20Yermak%20for%20two%20years%2C%20in%20charge%20of%20strategic%20communications%20on%20national%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Yermak%2C%20Arestovych%20told%20me%2C%20is%20also%20a%20master%20of%20using%20%26quot%3Bblack%20propaganda%26quot%3B%20to%20neutralize%20perceived%20rivals.%20In%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20war%2C%20the%20telegenic%20Arestovych%20became%20the%20country's%20unofficial%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmeduza.io%2Fen%2Ffeature%2F2023%2F01%2F20%2Ftrickster-actor-spokesman-spy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etherapist%20in%20chief%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20holding%20daily%20YouTube%20briefings%20assuring%20Ukrainians%20his%20country%20would%20soon%20prevail.%20By%20his%20telling%2C%20his%20ascent%20was%20viewed%20by%20Yermak%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20popular%20regard%20for%20Zelensky.%20Reports%20soon%20circulated%20in%20the%20Ukrainian%20media%20that%20Arestovych%20was%20a%20Russian%20agent%20%E2%80%94%20the%20worst%20sin%20imaginable%2C%20given%20the%20national%20mood.%20No%20matter%20that%20Arestovych%20had%20fought%20on%20the%20front%20lines%20against%20Russia%20in%202014%2C%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-hide-his-pleasure-over-republican-moves-block-ukraine-aid-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Vladimir%20Putin%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20fomented%20a%20separatist%20insurgency%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine.%20The%20damage%20was%20done%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20Arestovych%20held%20Yermak%20accountable%20for%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esmears.%20Yermak%2C%20he%20told%20me%2C%20is%20a%20two-sided%20person%2C%20%26quot%3Bevil%20and%20good%20together.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Arestovych's%20perspective%2C%20a%20key%20to%20understanding%20his%20former%20boss%20is%20Yermak's%20Russianness.%20Like%20Zelensky%2C%20his%20first%20language%20is%20Russian.%20With%20nationalist%20passions%20in%20Ukraine%20running%20high%2C%20some%20Ukrainians%20refuse%20to%20speak%20the%20tongue%20of%20its%20invader.%20Yet%20Yermak%20and%20Zelensky%20talk%20to%20each%20other%20in%20Russian%3B%20it%20was%20also%20the%20language%20spoken%20in%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20President%2C%20Arestovych%20told%20me%2C%20when%20he%20worked%20there.%20He%20says%20Yermak%20and%20his%20key%20deputies%20exhibit%20a%20%26quot%3Bstyle%20of%20behavior%2C%20style%20of%20management%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20%26quot%3Bis%20completely%20Russian%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20them%20think%20of%20people%20as%20chess%20pieces.%26quot%3B%20Another%20former%20official%20in%20the%20Zelensky%20administration%20also%20described%20Yermak%20to%20me%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20kind%20of%20Russian-Soviet%20type%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0meaning%20someone%20who%20prefers%20a%20Byzantine%2C%20cloaked%20method%20of%20operation%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20a%20more%20modern%2C%20open%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202021%2C%20Roman%20Chervinsky%2C%20a%20former%20officer%20in%20Ukraine's%20chief%20directorate%20of%20intelligence%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbykvu.com%2Feng%2Fbukvy%2Fex-intelligence-officer-alleges-yermak-can-be-russian-spy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evoiced%20allegations%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Yermak%20might%20have%20spied%20for%20Russia%20by%20supplying%20the%20enemy%20with%20details%20of%20a%20Ukrainian%20plan%20to%20entrap%20Russian%20mercenaries%20in%20Belarus.%20In%20April%2C%20Chervinsky%20was%20arrested%20on%20charges%20of%20exceeding%20his%20authority%20in%20an%20operation%20to%20try%20to%20get%20a%20Russian%20pilot%20to%20defect%20to%20Ukraine.%20Yermak%20has%20said%20allegations%20he%20has%20cooperated%20with%20Russia's%20security%20service%20are%20part%20of%20a%20Russian%20disinformation%20campaign%20and%20%26quot%3Bfunny%20for%20me%20to%20hear.%26quot%3B%20His%20advisor%2C%20Zarivna%2C%20told%20me%20Chervinsky%20was%20involved%20%26quot%3Bwith%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20oligarchic%20groups%20that%20advances%20its%20selfish%20agenda%26quot%3B%20in%20Ukraine.%20But%20she%20named%20no%20such%20group%20and%20neither%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20this%20matter%2C%20did%20Vasyl%20Maliuk%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Security%20Service%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20known%20as%20the%20SBU.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Zarivna's%20suggestion%2C%20I%20also%20spoke%20on%20Zoom%20with%20General%20Kyrylo%20Budanov%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Main%20Directorate%20of%20Intelligence%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20of%20Ukraine.%20He%20told%20me%20that%20an%20exhaustive%20internal%20investigation%20definitively%20proved%20that%20Chervinsky's%20allegation%20against%20Yermak%20as%20a%20Russian%20spy%20was%20false.%20And%20then%20he%20inquired%20about%20my%20Zoom%20wallpaper%2C%20in%20particular%20a%20portrait%20of%20the%20writer%20Anton%20Chekhov%20and%20a%20carved%20figure%20of%20a%20bear.%20These%20were%20Russian%20symbols%2C%20he%20said%2C%20to%20which%20I%20responded%20that%20my%20wallpaper%20also%20contained%20a%20Ukrainian%20symbol%2C%20of%20a%20painted%20hollowed%20out%20egg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlease%20understand%2C%20I%20told%20him%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20war%20is%20horrible.%20I%20think%20Putin%20is%20a%20bastard.%26quot%3B%20He%20responded%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20really%20glad%20you%20have%20that%20specific%20position%20supportive%20of%20Ukraine.%20As%20a%20journalist%2C%20I%20hope%20you%20will%20do%20the%20maximum%20in%20your%20craft%20not%20to%20create%20another%20information%20precedent%20which%20will%20be%20exploited%20by%20the%20Russians.%20Russians%2C%20they%20love%20these%20interesting%20stories.%20They%20twist%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20war%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYermak%20came%20under%20fire%20for%20the%20air%20of%20corruption%20that%20seemed%20to%20surround%20him.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20Kyiv%20Post%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20scandal%20it%20dubbed%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.kyivpost.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fop-ed%2Fbohdan-nahaylo-yermakgate-scandal-rocks-zelensky-administration.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYermakgate%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0reported%20on%20videos%20of%20Yermak's%20younger%20brother%2C%20Denys%2C%20appearing%20to%20discuss%20bribes%20in%20return%20for%20landing%20people%20jobs%20with%20the%20government%20and%20state-controlled%20companies.%20%26quot%3BAndriy%20Yermak%20insists%20he%20was%20not%20involved%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20paper%20reported%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20his%20brother%20was%20acting%20independently.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20publication%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ealso%20blasted%20Yermak%20for%20what%20it%20called%20%26quot%3Ba%20tactless%20display%20of%20ostentation.%26quot%3B%20His%20crime%3F%20%26quot%3BHe%20acquired%20a%20new%20Mercedes%20valued%20at%20almost%203%20million%20hrv%2C%20or%20over%20%24100%2C000.%26quot%3B%20Zarivna%20noted%20that%20Yermak%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Ba%20successful%20businessman%2C%20and%20he%20could%20afford%20such%20a%20car.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224253%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Adviser%20to%20Office%20of%20President%20of%20Ukraine%20Oleksii%20Arestovych%20seen%20at%20the%20site%20of%20the%20explosion%20of%20Russian%20missiles%20after%20a%20Russian%20missile%20attack%20in%20central%20Kyiv.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657b63567a3c8094d5dd2b5e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222835%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOleksiy%20Arestovych%2C%20Yermak's%20former%20advisor%2C%20calls%20him%20a%20master%20of%20using%20%26quot%3Bblack%20propaganda%26quot%3B%20to%20neutralize%20rivals.%3Cp%3EOleksii%20Chumachenko%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20the%20full-scale%20invasion%20began%2C%20Yermakgate%20quickly%20receded.%20The%20Western%20press%2C%20partial%20to%20tales%20of%20a%20heroic%20Ukraine%20under%20siege%2C%20tended%20to%20avert%20its%20eye%20from%20the%20seamy%20prewar%20tales%20involving%20Zelensky's%20closest%20advisor.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20White%20House%20wants%20to%20talk%20to%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fzelenskys-no-2-turns-to-celebrities-as-well-as-politicians-to-help-ukraine-ccc1ecff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofile%20in%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20in%20June%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20calls%20Andriy%20Yermak.%26quot%3B%20The%20piece%20noted%20that%20Yermak%20%26quot%3Bearned%20capital%20in%20the%20West%26quot%3B%20for%20helping%20to%20evacuate%20Americans%20during%20the%20US%20military's%20frantic%20withdrawal%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fafghanistan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAfghanistan%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%2C%20and%20cited%20his%20reputation%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bfilm%20buff%26quot%3B%20with%20%26quot%3Ba%20particular%20love%20of%20Italian%20movies%20%E2%80%94%20Fellini%20rather%20than%20Visconti.%26quot%3B%20There%20was%20no%20mention%20of%20the%20scandal%20involving%20his%20brother%2C%20or%20Chervinsky's%20allegation%20that%20he%20had%20served%20as%20a%20Russian%20agent%2C%20or%20his%20reputation%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20oligarchs.%20Instead%2C%20the%20Journal%20cited%20Yermak's%20quest%20%26quot%3Bto%20overhaul%20the%20unwieldy%20bureaucracy%20of%20the%20presidential%20office.%26quot%3B%20The%20man%20viewed%20by%20critics%20in%20Kyiv%20as%20the%20face%20of%20political%20corruption%20was%20being%20hailed%20as%20a%20champion%20of%20good%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOligarchs%20have%20been%20deeply%20intertwined%20in%20Ukrainian%20politics%20ever%20since%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20three%20decades%20ago.%20The%20basic%20formula%20is%20simple.%20%26quot%3BA%20question%20of%20power%20is%20a%20question%20of%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Arestovych%20explained%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20a%20question%20of%20money%20is%20a%20question%20of%20power.%26quot%3B%20The%20fancy%20term%20for%20this%20sleazy%20method%20of%20rule%20is%20%26quot%3Bpatronalism%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20feudal-like%20system%20in%20which%20rival%20clans%2C%20individually%20tied%20together%20by%20personal%20loyalties%2C%20predominate%20over%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Zelensky's%20rise%20to%20power%2C%20the%20business%20oligarchy%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20as%20in%20other%20post-Soviet%20countries%2C%20operated%20on%20a%20spoils%20system%20that%20amounted%20to%20might%20makes%20right.%20There%20was%20little%20incentive%20for%20an%20honest%20entrepreneur%20to%20launch%20a%20company%20with%20the%20knowledge%20that%2C%20with%20the%20company's%20success%2C%20one%20of%20the%20clans%20might%20muscle%20in%20on%20the%20venture%20and%20seize%20control%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20legal%20protections%20were%20on%20the%20books.%20As%20clan%20leaders%20became%20billionaires%2C%20through%20their%20capture%20of%20industrial%20and%20financial%20assets%2C%20Ukraine%20remained%20desperately%20poor%2C%20its%20wealth%20routinely%20pumped%20out%20of%20the%20country%20into%20offshore%20accounts.%20In%202018%2C%20the%20year%20before%20Zelensky's%20election%2C%20Ukraine%20ranked%20as%20the%20poorest%20country%20in%20Europe%2C%20with%20a%20GDP%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20just%20below%20%243%2C000%20%E2%80%94%C2%A08%25%20lower%20than%20that%20of%20Moldova%2C%20the%20second%20poorest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20inherent%20murkiness%20to%20oligarchic%20structures%20wherever%20they%20arise%2C%20as%20I%20discovered%20in%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20during%20my%20time%20as%20Moscow%20bureau%20chief%20of%20Business%20Week.%20One%20day%2C%20I%20received%20a%20call%20from%20a%20business%20magnate%20who%20told%20me%20his%20life%20was%20at%20risk%20over%20a%20dispute%20involving%20the%20privatization%20of%20a%20vegetable-oil%20factory%20in%20the%20Ukrainian%20seaport%20of%20Odesa.%20Intrigued%2C%20I%20hopped%20on%20a%20flight%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20came%20nowhere%20close%20to%20getting%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20matter.%20(I%20also%20declined%2C%20to%20the%20astonishment%20of%20my%20host%2C%20the%20services%20of%20a%20prostitute%20he%20had%20taken%20it%20upon%20himself%20to%20hire%20as%20a%20gift.)%20A%20decade%20later%2C%20on%20a%20second%20reporting%20trip%20to%20Odesa%2C%20I%20asked%20my%20Ukrainian%20companion%20for%20the%20name%20of%20the%20biggest%20owner%20of%20assets%20in%20the%20sprawling%20industrial%20city.%20The%20answer%2C%20he%20told%20me%2C%20was%20Ihor%20Kolomoisky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKolomoisky%20enjoyed%20a%20reputation%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20ruthless%20of%20the%20oligarchs%20in%20post-Soviet%20Ukraine.%20He%20had%20amassed%20substantial%20holdings%20in%20metals%2C%20banks%2C%20airlines%2C%20energy%2C%20and%20media.%20He%20was%20also%20connected%20to%20Zelensky%3A%20His%201%2B1%20Media%20Group%20included%20a%20Ukrainian%20television%20channel%20that%20broadcast%20Zelensky's%20scripted%20shows%20and%20championed%20his%20run%20for%20the%20presidency.%20More%20than%20a%20few%20insiders%20in%20Kyiv's%20political%2C%20business%2C%20and%20media%20circles%20regarded%20Kolomoisky%20as%20the%20real%20victor%20of%20Zelensky's%20improbable%20triumph%2C%20the%20modern-day%20robber%20baron%20who%20would%20now%20run%20Ukraine%20behind%20his%20likable%20front%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20interpretation%20was%20probably%20always%20wrong.%20Zelensky's%20comedy%20drew%20on%20his%20withering%20portraits%20of%20oligarch%20types%2C%20and%20he%20campaigned%20as%20the%20candidate%20who%20would%20rid%20Ukraine%20of%20these%20despised%20parasites.%20Once%20in%20office%2C%20he%20seemed%20to%20make%20good%20on%20that%20vow.%20In%202021%2C%20he%20pushed%20through%20a%20law%20to%20require%20publication%20of%20a%20public%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eregister%20of%20oligarchs%2C%20which%20would%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebrand%20them%20as%20detriments%20to%20the%20social%20welfare.%20After%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine%2C%20he%20signed%20a%20decree%20requiring%20all%20broadcasts%20by%20national%20television%20channels%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0mostly%20owned%20by%20the%20oligarchs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0to%20be%20approved%20by%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20President.%20Given%20the%20unpromising%20turn%20of%20events%2C%20one%20prominent%20oligarch%2C%20Rinat%20Akhmetov%2C%20often%20said%20to%20be%20Ukraine's%20richest%20man%2C%20sold%20off%20all%20his%20media%20holdings%2C%20including%20the%20country's%20largest%20television%20channel.%20Then%2C%20in%20September%2C%20just%20two%20weeks%20before%20I%20arrived%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20the%20SBU%20arrested%20Kolomoisky%20on%20charges%20of%20fraud%20and%20money%20laundering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ihor%20Kolomoyskyi%20during%20his%20trial.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657c79c550edbc52a864c0aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIhor%20Kolomoisky%2C%20widely%20regarded%20as%20one%20of%20Ukraine's%20most%20ruthless%20oligarchs%2C%20was%20arrested%20in%20September%20on%20charges%20of%20money%20laundering.%3Cp%3EYan%20Dobronosov%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWashington%20applauded%20the%20move%3B%20Kolomoisky%20had%20already%20been%20blacklisted%20by%20the%20State%20Department%2C%20made%20ineligible%20to%20enter%20the%20United%20States%20%26quot%3Bdue%20to%20his%20involvement%20in%20significant%20corruption%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20declared%20in%202021.%20But%20as%20I%20learned%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20opinion%20was%20split%20on%20the%20meaning%20of%20Kolomoisky's%20seizure%20by%20the%20SBU.%20Some%20insiders%20thought%20Zelensky%20was%20tossing%20Washington%20a%20bone%20to%20prove%20he%20was%20serious%20about%20tackling%20corruption.%20Others%20viewed%20the%20arrest%20as%20a%20cagy%20operation%20by%20the%20Yermak%20clan%20to%20take%20out%20a%20rival.%20One%20of%20Yermak's%20top%20deputies%2C%20Oleh%20Tatarov%2C%20oversees%20the%20SBU.%20Tatarov%20has%20himself%20been%20accused%20of%20corruption%3A%20The%20CEO%20of%20one%20of%20Ukraine's%20biggest%20construction%20firms%20told%20Reuters%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fgraft-accusations-dog-top-zelenskiy-aides-2023-09-19%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETatarov%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20bribed%20public%20officials%20with%20rolls%20of%20American%20cash%20to%20get%20building%20projects%20approved.%20Tatarov%20has%20denied%20doing%20anything%20wrong%20and%20said%20political%20opponents%20are%20trying%20to%20settle%20scores.%20His%20accuser%20also%20faces%20allegations%20of%20corruption%20involving%20the%20construction%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYermak%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20has%20insisted%20Zelensky%20has%20%26quot%3Bzero%20tolerance%20for%20corruption.%26quot%3B%20He%20pointed%2C%20as%20evidence%2C%20to%20the%20arrest%20in%20May%20of%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20bribery%20charges%2C%20in%20a%20case%20brought%20by%20federal%20anti-corruption%20prosecutors.%20%26quot%3BThe%20US%20taxpayers%20have%20the%20right%20to%20know%20what%20they%20pay%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Zarivna%20told%20me%20in%20response%20to%20my%20question%20about%20how%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20President%20responded%20to%20the%20September%20letter%20sent%20by%20the%20Biden%20White%20House%20on%20the%20need%20for%20reforms%20to%20counter%20corruption.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20reporting%20every%20cent%20spent%2C%20and%20open%20for%20an%20independent%20audit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20battle%20over%20corruption%20in%20Ukraine%20stems%2C%20in%20part%2C%20from%20a%20deep%20cultural%20divide%20within%20the%20country.%20It%20is%20undoubtedly%20the%20case%2C%20as%20Yermak%20says%2C%20that%20the%20Kremlin's%20propagandists%20in%20Moscow%20strive%20to%20depict%20Zelensky's%20government%20as%20a%20den%20of%20thieves.%20Nevertheless%2C%20the%20perspective%20that%20Yermak%20is%20building%20an%20oligarchic%20clan%20with%20the%20help%20of%20dubious%20deputies%20like%20Tatarov%20tends%20to%20come%20from%20the%20most%20cosmopolitan%2C%20Western-oriented%2C%20well-educated%2C%20and%20well-connected%20segment%20of%20Ukrainian%20society%2C%20the%20sort%20of%20people%20who%20speak%20English%20fluently%20and%20feel%20at%20home%20in%20Europe%20and%20America.%20They%20are%20generally%20too%20young%20to%20have%20experienced%20the%20full%20force%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20Yulia%20Klymenko%2C%20an%20opposition%20member%20of%20parliament%20who%20fits%20that%20profile%20%E2%80%94%20she%20has%20represented%20the%20European%20Bank%20for%20Reconstruction%20and%20Development%20and%20served%20on%20the%20Ukrainian%20chapter%20of%20the%20board%20of%20Transparency%20International%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0told%20me%20that%20Zelensky%20had%20squandered%20a%20historic%20opportunity%20to%20dismiss%20the%20%26quot%3Bcrooks%20and%20idiots%26quot%3B%20who%20controlled%20the%20government%20at%20every%20level.%20She%20said%20he%20is%20instead%20using%20martial%20law%20to%20perpetuate%20his%20own%20rule.%20Two%20days%20after%20we%20spoke%2C%20the%20Zelensky-aligned%20chairman%20of%20the%20parliament%20said%20that%20implementation%20of%20the%20landmark%20anti-oligarchs%20law%2C%20including%20publication%20of%20a%20register%20of%20oligarchs%2C%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rferl.org%2Fa%2Fukraine-anti-oligarch-law-stefanchuk-venice-commission%2F32605997.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuspended%20until%20after%20the%20war%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoman%20Ilto%2C%20another%20cosmopolitan%20type%2C%20works%20for%20the%20Swedish%20Embassy%20in%20Kyiv%20on%20energy%20and%20environmental%20issues.%20Unlike%20many%20critics%20of%20the%20oligarchs%2C%20he%20witnessed%20their%20rise%20firsthand.%20In%20the%20early%202000s%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eafter%20studying%20at%20Harvard%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20Ukraine%20to%20work%20for%20a%20steel%20and%20mining%20company.%20That%20was%20his%20first%20exposure%20to%20%26quot%3Bclan%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me%20over%20breakfast%20at%20my%20hotel%20in%20central%20Kyiv.%20In%20those%20days%2C%20listening%20to%20the%20incessant%20talk%20about%20the%20rivalry%20between%20Kolomoisky%20and%20Akhmetov%2C%20he%20began%20to%20understand%20oligarchs%20as%20the%20organizing%20principle%20of%20Ukrainian%20political%20and%20economic%20life.%20In%202016%2C%20he%20joined%20Ukrnafta%2C%20the%20state-controlled%20oil%20and%20natural-gas%20giant%2C%20and%20spent%20nearly%20seven%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eyears%20there%2C%20including%20stints%20as%20head%20of%20government%20relations%20and%20investor%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20war%20began%2C%20Ilto%20said%2C%20control%20of%20the%20energy%20sector%20has%20been%20seized%20by%20a%20%26quot%3Bnascent%26quot%3B%20oligarchic%20clan%20led%20by%20Yermak.%20Under%20a%20national%20security%20decree%20issued%20by%20Zelensky%2C%20the%20state%20had%20assumed%20full%20ownership%20of%20Ukrnafta%20and%20other%20strategically%20important%20companies.%20Perhaps%2C%20Ilto%20allowed%2C%20temporary%20nationalization%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bnecessary%20evil%26quot%3B%20to%20keep%20the%20military%20supplied%20with%20oil%20and%20other%20vital%20resources.%20%26quot%3BStill%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20wonder%20why%20there%20is%20no%20proper%20supervisory%20board%2C%20there%20are%20no%20proper%20controls.%20That%20is%20a%20perfect%20environment%20for%20corruption%20and%20wrongdoing%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20for%20classic%20oligarch%20maneuvers%20like%20siphoning%20off%20assets%20from%20a%20state-run%20property.%20In%20October%2C%20about%20a%20month%20after%20my%20conversation%20with%20Ilto%2C%20Ukrnafta's%20leadership%20announced%20that%20an%20independent%20supervisory%20board%20would%20be%20formed%20for%20the%20company%20by%20the%20end%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIlto%20flagged%20another%20top%20Yermak%20deputy%2C%20Rostyslav%20Shurma%2C%20who%20served%20the%20Akhmetov%20clan%20for%20years%20before%20assuming%20oversight%20of%20energy%20and%20other%20sectors%20of%20the%20economy%20for%20the%20Office%20for%20the%20President.%20Like%20Oleh%20Tatarov%2C%20Shurma%20is%20cited%20in%20Kyiv%20circles%20as%20another%20cog%20in%20the%20Yermak%20machine.%20%26quot%3BHe%20kind%20of%20acts%20as%20a%20cashier%20for%20Yermak%20and%20the%20Office%20of%20President%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20an%20ex-Zelensky%20government%20official%20who%20declined%20to%20go%20on%20the%20record%20for%20fear%2C%20he%20said%2C%20of%20becoming%20a%20target%20of%20the%20Yermak%20team.%20In%20a%20lengthy%20September%20piece%2C%20Ukrainska%20Pravda%20portrayed%20Shurma%20as%20a%20mini-empire%20builder.%20The%20paper%2C%20which%20is%20owned%20by%20a%20private-equity%20firm%20headed%20by%20a%20Czech-born%20businessman%20who%20served%20on%20the%20board%20of%20Transparency%20International%20Ukraine%2C%20cited%20a%20%26quot%3Bscandal%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20the%20state%20bought%20electricity%20from%20solar%20plants%20co-owned%20by%20Shurma's%20brother%2C%20even%20though%20the%20plants%20were%20no%20longer%20connected%20to%20the%20Ukraine%20energy%20grid.%20Asked%20by%20Time%20about%20the%20matter%2C%20Shurma%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bpiece%20of%20shit%26quot%3B%20thrown%20at%20him%20by%20Zelensky's%20political%20enemies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Ukraine%2C%20as%20in%20Russia%2C%20conspiracy%20thinking%20is%20an%20inevitable%20byproduct%20of%20years%20of%20oligarchic%20rule.%20One%20source%20in%20Kyiv%20assured%20me%20that%20the%20nation's%20gambling%20operations%20were%20secretly%20funneling%20bitcoin%20to%20the%20Zelensky%20team%20in%20exchange%20for%20favorable%20tax%20treatment.%20No%20one%20was%20able%20to%20substantiate%20the%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20back%20in%20the%20States%2C%20I%20found%20it%20hard%20to%20dismiss%20the%20widespread%20anxieties%20over%20the%20rise%20of%20a%20new%20oligarchy.%20Was%20Ukraine%2C%20even%20under%20a%20professed%20anti-oligarch%20president%2C%20really%20so%20different%20from%20Russia%20and%20other%20post-Soviet%20countries%2C%20where%20state-controlled%20companies%20serve%20as%20notorious%20havens%20for%20siphoning%20off%20critical%20assets%3F%20It%20could%20be%2C%20as%20some%20people%20in%20Kyiv%20are%20convinced%2C%20that%20the%20Zelensky-Yermak%20team%20is%20building%20its%20own%20clan%20%26quot%3Bto%20basically%20out%20oligarch%20the%20oligarchs%2C%26quot%3B%20Henry%20Hale%2C%20a%20specialist%20in%20Ukraine%20at%20George%20Washington%20University%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223978%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Head%20Office%20of%20the%20President%20of%20Ukraine%20Andriy%20Yermak%20speaks%20during%20an%20interview%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20August%2022%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657b64d850edbc52a8646a36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222530%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20White%20House%20is%20counting%20on%20Yermak%20to%20root%20out%20systemic%20corruption.%20But%20he%20may%20be%20trying%20to%20%26quot%3Bout%20oligarch%20the%20oligarchs%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20Ukraine%20specialist%20at%20George%20Washington%20University.%3Cp%3EMetin%20Aktas%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20in%20Washington%20are%20certainly%20worried%20about%20American%20tax%20dollars%20disappearing%20down%20a%20rabbit%20hole%20of%20Ukrainian%20corruption.%20%26quot%3BAre%20we%20concerned%20about%20the%20protection%20of%20taxpayer%20money%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Latesha%20Love-Grayer%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edirector%20of%20international%20affairs%20and%20trade%20at%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office.%20%26quot%3BAbsolutely.%26quot%3B%20The%20congressional%20watchdog%20agency%2C%20she%20told%20me%2C%20is%20participating%20in%20monthly%20meetings%20on%20the%20issue%20with%20representatives%20from%20the%20State%20Department%2C%20the%20Defense%20Department%2C%20and%20the%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development.%20She%20noted%20that%20Iraq%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20Haiti%2C%20and%20Bosnia%20and%20Herzegovina%20all%20offered%20cautionary%20examples%20of%20the%20potential%20for%20corruption%20in%20war-reconstruction%20efforts.%20Yet%20when%20I%20offered%20that%20a%20new%20oligarchic%20regime%20appeared%20to%20be%20arising%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20centered%20in%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20President%2C%20Love-Grayer%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erefrained%20from%20comment.%20Her%20team%20has%20yet%20to%20set%20foot%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20she%20said%2C%20or%20to%20meet%20with%20government%20officials%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Biden%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20political%20corruption%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20both%20deeply%20familiar%20and%20especially%20thorny.%20As%20vice%20president%2C%20Biden%20handled%20the%20Ukraine%20portfolio%20for%20the%20Obama%20administration%20from%202009%20to%202017.%20In%202015%2C%20a%20career%20State%20Department%20official%20raised%20concerns%20with%20a%20Biden%20aide%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunter-bidens-tax-returns-reveal-debt-kevin-morris-irs-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHunter%20Biden%3C%2Fa%3E's%20service%20on%20the%20board%20of%20the%20energy%20firm%20Burisma%20could%20complicate%20President%20Barack%20Obama's%20efforts%20to%20prod%20Kyiv%20into%20battling%20corruption.%20But%20the%20official%2C%20who%20later%20related%20the%20story%20in%20closed-door%20testimony%20to%20Congress%2C%20said%20the%20aide%20told%20him%20Joe%20Biden%20did%20not%20have%20the%20%26quot%3Bbandwidth%26quot%3B%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20matter%20involving%20his%20younger%20son%20as%20his%20older%20one%2C%20Beau%2C%20was%20dealing%20with%20cancer.%20It%20was%20a%20desire%20to%20dig%20up%20political%20dirt%20like%20this%20on%20Hunter%20Biden's%20activities%20in%20Ukraine%20that%20led%20Trump%20to%20threaten%20to%20withhold%20military%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eaid%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20leading%20to%20his%20first%20impeachment.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E(The%20White%20House%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20repeated%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Erequests%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20worst-case%20scenario%20for%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20very%2C%20very%20%26quot%3Bbad%20story%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20that%20Yermak's%20oligarchic%20bent%20intensifies%20to%20the%20point%20that%20Washington%20and%20allies%20in%20Europe%20retreat%20both%20from%20continued%20military%20assistance%20and%20from%20plans%20to%20pour%20massive%20amounts%20of%20aid%20into%20the%20country%20for%20postwar%20reconstruction.%20The%20Zelensky%20government%2C%20in%20response%2C%20ushers%20in%20yet%20another%20sorry%20chapter%20of%20corrupt%2C%20parasitic%20rule%20in%20post-Soviet%20Ukraine.%20Membership%20in%20the%20European%20Union%20becomes%20an%20impossible%20dream.%20Despairing%20citizens%20turn%20to%20violence%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20topple%20their%20oppressors.%20Ironically%2C%20it's%20a%20scenario%20with%20an%20eerie%20echo%20of%20how%20Russia%20under%20Putin%20devolved%20into%20the%20state-girded%20oligarchy%20it%20has%20become%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20that%20way.%20A%20crucial%20difference%20between%20Russia%20in%20the%20Putin%20era%20and%20today's%20Ukraine%20is%20that%20Putin%20has%20crushed%20Russia's%20civil%20society.%20The%20press%20is%20cowed%3B%20anti-Putin%20political%20activists%20are%20imprisoned%20or%20exiled.%20In%20Ukraine%2C%20even%20as%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20President%20maintains%20wartime%20control%20of%20TV%20broadcasts%2C%20civil%20society%20remains%20vibrant.%20News%20outlets%20have%20trained%20their%20investigative%20sights%20on%20the%20Yermak%20crew.%20Anti-corruption%20groups%20abound%2C%20not%20only%20in%20Kyiv%20but%20in%20big%20cities%20like%20Kharkiv.%20Opposition%20figures%20in%20parliament%2C%20along%20with%20critics%20of%20the%20Zelensky%20government%20in%20the%20business%20and%20financial%20communities%2C%20are%20%C2%A0for%20the%20most%20part%20not%20afraid%20to%20make%20their%20voices%20heard.%20It's%20possible%20there%20will%20be%20a%20peaceful%20reckoning%2C%20one%20that%20will%20force%20the%20ouster%20of%20Yermak%20and%20his%20underlings%20and%20speed%20Ukraine's%20integration%20into%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20counter%20corruption%2C%20some%20in%20Ukraine%20are%20calling%20for%20the%20European%20Union%20to%20play%20a%20strong%2C%20even%20decisive%2C%20role%20in%20the%20postwar%20rebuilding%20of%20Ukraine.%20The%20EU%2C%20Roman%20Ilto%20told%20me%2C%20should%20create%20and%20administer%20a%20Ukraine-reconstruction%20agency%20for%20the%20management%20of%20rebuilding%20projects%2C%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20funds%20for%20the%20work%20do%20not%20fall%20into%20the%20wrong%20hands.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20people%20would%20be%20happy%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20power%20plants%20are%20rebuilt%2C%20the%20roads%20are%20rebuilt%2C%20housing%20is%20rebuilt%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20country%20is%20on%20a%20path%20to%20the%20European%20Union.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainians%20remain%20painfully%20aware%20of%20their%20reputation%20on%20the%20world%20stage.%20%26quot%3BPlease%20remember%20that%20not%20all%20Ukrainians%20are%20crooks%20and%20idiots%20%3A)%2C%26quot%3B%20Klymenko%2C%20the%20opposition%20lawmaker%2C%20texted%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20decent%20people%20who%20love%20our%20country%26quot%3B%20and%20are%20committed%20to%20building%20a%20free%20society%2C%20she%20said.%20That%2C%20of%20course%2C%20requires%20not%20only%20fair%20elections%20and%20an%20unrestrained%20press%2C%20but%20also%20freedom%20from%20the%20malign%20clutches%20of%20oligarchy.%20Ukrainians%20know%20from%20long%20and%20bitter%20experience%20that%20political%20independence%20means%20little%20without%20economic%20democracy.%20The%20Soviet%20Union%20bequeathed%20to%20the%20country%20a%20legacy%20of%20state%20corruption.%20Even%20if%20Ukraine%20succeeds%20at%20defeating%20Russia%2C%20the%20oligarchs%20could%20still%20win%20the%20war%20for%20its%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fpaul-starobin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPaul%20Starobin%3C%2Fem%3E%